<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
BOLIVIA; 
</P>
<P>
TRAFFICKERS' PLOT TO KILL PRESIDENT TOLD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The government is probing an alleged plot by cocaine traffickers to assassinate 
President Jaime Paz Zamora, U.S. Ambassador Robert S. Gelbard and others, the 
head of Bolivia's special anti-drug force said. Retired Gen. Lucio Anez said he 
was also on the alleged death list, along with Interior Minister Guillermo 
Capobianco Ribera and other officials. Officials said the plot was hatched in 
Miami by former Interior Minister Luis Arce Gomez, who was extradited to the 
United States on drug-trafficking charges in December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
