<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
INDIA; 
</P>
<P>
60 DIE IN TRAIN FIRE SET BY PROTESTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 60 people burned to death when leftist radicals set fire to a train 
car in a protest that went awry near the south Indian city of Hyderabad, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
They said Maoists poured kerosene on the floor of the car after boarding it to 
distribute leaflets supporting government plans to increase jobs reserved for 
lower-caste Hindus. The Maoists told the 120 to 150 passengers in the car to 
get out, set the kerosene on fire, then jumped off. Panic ensued when 
passengers were unable to open five of the six car doors, police quoted 
survivors as saying. 
</P>
</TEXT>
