<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
FRANCE; 
</P>
<P>
YOUTHS RIOT FOR 4TH STRAIGHT NIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rampaging youths torched a tobacco shop and a store in the shopping center of a 
low-income suburb of Lyon, France, in the fourth straight night of unrest. 
</P>
<P>
The violence was far less severe than on the three previous nights, however, 
when hundreds of stone-throwing youths set fire to 20 buildings and burned two 
dozen cars. The rioting was triggered by the weekend death of Thomas Claudio, 
21, a passenger on a motorcycle that collided with a police patrol car. The 
rioters blame police for the death. 
</P>
</TEXT>
