<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
CHINA; 
</P>
<P>
FUGITIVE EMBEZZLER BLAMED IN HIJACKING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Officials said a fugitive embezzler hijacked a jetliner and caused its crash 
last week in Canton, killing 128. 
</P>
<P>
Canton's aviation bureau and public security bureau identified the hijacker as 
Jiang Xiaofeng, 21, a purchasing agent for a county government office in 
Changsha. It said he was wanted by Chinese police for embezzling $3,600 in 
July. Jiang boarded a Boeing 737 in Xiamen and demanded to be taken to Taiwan, 
the officials said. Low on fuel, the plane landed instead in Canton, striking 
two planes on the ground. 
</P>
</TEXT>
