<TEXT>
<P>
Parting Is Such Sweet Sorrow: Jonathan Miller, artistic director of the Old Vic 
Theater in London since January, 1988, has resigned after the theater's owner, 
David Mirvish, announced last weekend that the last two productions of the 
season would be scrapped because of financial difficulties. Miller, who had 
planned to leave at the end of the season in March, was quoted in the London 
Daily Telegraph as saying, "Now that the two plays have been cancelled I am 
leaving right away since there is no point in my staying." CLAUDIA PUIG 
