<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Allan Bristow, an executive for the Charlotte Hornets, has apologized for 
grabbing and pushing the agent for first-round draft pick Kendall Gill during 
negotiations Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Bristow offered to pay medical expenses resulting from the incident involving 
agent Arn Tellem, the NBA said. 
</P>
<P>
"We were negotiating hard on behalf of our clients and I guess I got carried 
away," Bristow said. "Arn conducted himself professionally at all times, and I 
know that I was wrong and I'm sorry." 
</P>
<P>
Tellem said Bristow's statement "closes the incident." 
</P>
<P>
"I just want to get back to business as usual and make sure Gill is signed as 
soon as possible," the agent said. 
</P>
<P>
The league did not say if Tellem was injured during the incident in Charlotte, 
but earlier reports said he suffered a sprained neck. 
</P>
<P>
NBA Commissioner David Stern said no action would be taken against Bristow. 
