<HEADLINE>
<P>
DOCTOR CLEARS LAKERS' SMITH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARK HEISLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HONOLULU 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rookie guard Tony Smith, who had been sent to Los Angeles for more tests after 
his preseason physical examination indicated an irregular heartbeat, was 
cleared by Laker physician Dr. Michael Mellman and returned to training camp 
Tuesday. Smith, the second-round draft choice from Marquette, was to resume 
practice without restriction. MARK HEISLER 
</P>
