<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
AROUND THE NATION; 
</P>
<P>
BLEDSOE REPLACES GOSSEN WITH COUGARS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Freshman Drew Bledsoe has replaced senior Brad Gossen as Washington State's 
starting quarterback. 
</P>
<P>
Bledsoe, one of the nation's top prep recruits last year, earned the starting 
job for his performance in a 30-17 loss to USC, Coach Mike Price said from 
Pullman, Wash., in a weekly telephone conference. 
</P>
<P>
"I think what we're going to do offensively in our game plan and what we want 
to do . . . is more the things that Drew Bledsoe does best," Price said. "We're 
going to try him out at it." 
</P>
<P>
Coming off the bench late against USC, Bledsoe threw for one touchdown and ran 
for another, completing six of 12 passes for 145 yards. 
</P>
<P>
Price said Bledsoe lacks experience, but knows the offense well enough to win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
