<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL REPORT; 
</P>
<P>
WEEKDAY UPDATE; 
</P>
<P>
UCLA; 
</P>
<P>
MADDOX IMPRESSES FRIENDS, FOES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Quarterback Tommy Maddox threw three interceptions when UCLA lost to Arizona, 
28-21, Saturday at the Rose Bowl. However, he earned the respect of an opponent 
and a teammate. 
</P>
<P>
Arizona free safety Jeff Hammerschmidt, who intercepted one of Maddox's passes, 
said the Bruin quarterback is the best his team has faced this year. "He's such 
a leader," Hammerschmidt said. "I don't know how many times he came up to the 
line, saw our defense and checked off to another play. 
</P>
<P>
"He's incredible, and the team really believes in him. He's just a big winner, 
and I can see why people love him over (in Los Angeles)." 
</P>
<P>
UCLA wide receiver Reggie Moore said last year's team didn't always believe it 
could win. "This was a hard loss for us," Moore said. "We thought all along we 
were going to win it. But we're not going to fold. This team isn't going to 
quit." 
</P>
<P>
He added that Maddox is a major reason for UCLA's new attitude. "Tommy has 
tremendous poise," he said. MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</TEXT>
