<HEADLINE>
<P>
10 SPRINTERS NAMED FOR ANCIENT TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BILL CHRISTINE, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With Housebuster injured, the Breeders' Cup Sprint has gone from a race with an 
odds-on favorite to a scramble, and a contender might emerge today from the 
$100,000 Ancient Title Breeders' Cup Handicap at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
The Ancient Title, which is at six furlongs, drew 10 starters. 
</P>
<P>
The favorites are Prospectors Gamble and Sensational Star. 
</P>
<P>
Prospectors Gamble, who won two of three stakes earlier this year at Hollywood 
Park, has returned to California from Saratoga, where the 5-year-old roan had a 
victory and a fourth-place finish in two tries. 
</P>
<P>
Sensational Star, a former claimer, has increased his earnings to $365,355 with 
three consecutive victories, the last two in sprints at Del Mar. He barely 
missed the track record for three-quarters of a mile with a time of 1:08 in the 
Bing Crosby Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
On Saturday at Santa Anita, Ruhlmann and Lively One will try to earn their way 
to the Breeders' Cup for trainer Charlie Whittingham when they run in the 
$200,000 Goodwood Handicap, and on Sunday, older fillies and mares will compete 
on the grass in the $150,000 Las Palmas Handicap. 
</P>
<P>
Starting today, after approval by the California Horse Racing Board, Santa 
Anita will offer its races for betting to Canterbury Downs in Minnesota and 
Birmingham Race Course in Alabama. Nevada's race books hope to be plugged into 
the same interstate network before the Oak Tree season ends, and all of the 
out-of-state bets will be included in the parimutuel pools at Santa Anita. 
</P>
</TEXT>
