<P>
RAMS UNLIKELY TO OBTAIN ALLEN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Despite another round of weekend rumors, there appears to be little chance 
running back Marcus Allen will become a Ram before next Tuesday's trading 
deadline. 
</P>
<P>
The Rams are ranked first in the NFL on offense, last on defense. 
</P>
<P>
They already have three former No. 1 draft choices in the backfield -- 
Cleveland Gary, Curt Warner and Gaston Green. Gary gained 92 yards in 20 
carries as the starting tailback against the Cincinnati Bengals on Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The most recent rumor concerning Allen and the Rams was reported by NBC 
correspondent and Boston Globe reporter Will McDonough, a long-time confidant 
of Raider owner Al Davis. 
</P>
<P>
The Raiders had reportedly offered Allen to the Rams last summer for linebacker 
Kevin Greene, then a holdout. The latest report has the Raiders reducing the 
offer to a first-round draft choice. 
</P>
<P>
The San Francisco 49ers might also be interested in trading for Allen, with 
running back Roger Craig's status uncertain. 
</P>
<P>
Raider Coach Art Shell said he is not sure how long the team will be without 
linebacker Ron Burton, who suffered a knee injury on the opening kickoff of the 
38-24 loss to the Bills in Buffalo Sunday night. CHRIS DUFRESNE 
</P>
</TEXT>
