<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
CHAPMAN WOMEN UPSET RIVERSIDE IN VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Debi Waller had 30 kills and 17 digs to lead Chapman College to an upset of UC 
Riverside, the No. 2-ranked women's volleyball team in Division II, in a 
California Collegiate Athletic Assn. match Tuesday at Chapman. 
</P>
<P>
Rena Strange added 18 kills as 14th-ranked Chapman (16-9, 1-1) won, 15-7, 15-7, 
14-16, 9-15, 15-11. 
</P>
<P>
In Big West Conference water polo: 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach 7, UC Irvine 5 -- It was the second consecutive Big West 
Conference loss and fourth loss in five games for the Anteaters (8-8, 1-2). 
Mike Burke scored four goals, including three in the first half, as Long Beach 
built a 5-1 lead. 
</P>
<P>
Goalkeeper Duff Harold had 20 saves for the 49ers (4-7, 2-1). 
</P>
<P>
Skylar Putman, Mark Herman, Tom Lowrey, Jay Warren and Steve Gill each scored 
for Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Christ College Irvine 6, Caltech 0 -- Aaron Clasen and Rodney Nelson each had 
two goals and Matt Richards and Kris Schneider each had one for visiting Christ 
College Irvine (2-9). 
</P>
</TEXT>
