<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
GROSSMONT ENDS OCC'S WATER POLO STREAK AT 47 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Orange Coast College water polo team's 47-game winning streak in Orange 
Empire Conference play under Coach Don Watson ended Tuesday as the Pirates lost 
to Grossmont, 12-9, at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
Watson's teams had won three titles and were 6-0 this season in conference 
before Tuesday's loss. 
</P>
<P>
Grossmont led, 5-4, at the half and stretched its lead to 9-6 after three 
quarters. Mike McNeff had three goals and Arturo Sanchez two for OCC (16-4, 
6-1). 
</P>
<P>
In another Orange Empire Conference match: 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 16, Rancho Santiago 13 -- Jason Armison, Fred Pieracci and Ron 
Johnson had three goals each for visiting Saddleback (5-11, 1-4). 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 10, Palomar 8 -- Brian Pickler had three goals for visiting Cypress 
(13-6, 4-2). 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference men's soccer: 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 2, Cypress 0 -- David Uzzi and Keith Barnes scored in the second half 
for host Fullerton (4-7-2, 2-3-1). 
</P>
<P>
Irvine Valley 2, Golden West 2 -- Kevin Martin and Jesus Silva scored in the 
first half for Golden West (0-3-2, 3-8-1), but Mike Densmore and Brad Wilson 
scored in the second half for host Irvine Valley (8-1-4, 1-1-3). 
</P>
</TEXT>
