<TEXT>
<P>
Kendall Gill, the Charlotte Hornets' top draft pick, suited up for practice 
today after the team announced that it had signed him to a four-year contract. 
</P>
<P>
The signing ends a five-day holdout by the 6-foot-5 guard from Illinois that 
featured a physical confrontation last week between Hornets executive Allan 
Bristow and Gill's agent, Arn Tellem. 
